article.description: Max Abmas scored 23 points and Oral Roberts held off Purdue-Fort Wayne, 72-66 in the regular season finale on Saturday night.
article.headline: Oral Roberts holds off Purdue-Fort Wayne in finale, 72-66
article.linkText: Oral Roberts holds off Purdue-Fort Wayne in finale, 72-66
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Max Abmas scored 23 points and Oral Roberts held off Purdue-Fort Wayne, 72-66 in the regular season finale on Saturday night. Oral Roberts won its fifth straight home win and clinched the No. 4 seed into the Summit League tournament, which will be held March 7-10 in Sioux Falls, S.D. The Golden Eagles will face No. 5 Omaha on March 8. R.J. Fuqua scored 20 points and Emmanuel Nzekwesi added another 19 for the Golden Eagles (16-13, 9-7). Jarred Godfrey paced the Mastodons (13-18, 6-10) with 21 points.
